people.description: Founder of the Kilkenny Academy, the first diocesan school in Ireland following the loosening of penal restrictions on education in 1782. This academy eventually developed to become the lay school within St. Kieran's College Kilkenny. Troy's exact date of birth in 1739 and his date of ordination (1757 or 1762) differ across sources. The latter ordination date is the most probable given his age.

people.description: Rev Smith travelled to Trinidad in 1827 where he ministered in Port-O-Spain. The following year he went to San Fernando, and in 1834 was appointed to the pastorship of Port-O-Spain. In 1837 he was promoted to Bishop of Agna, and in 1844 appointed Bishop of Olympus and Vicar Apostolic of the British & Danish West India Islands. In 1851 Smith was appointed Archbishop of Port-O-Spain; his archbishopric catering for Trinidad, Tobago, Grenada, St Lucia and St Vincent.
people.label: Richard Smith
